A survey of young children hospitalized with viral gastroentefitis, and o f the members of some o f their families, was carried out. Results showed rotavirus to be the principal agent associated with the condition though other types were also detected. In addition, rotavirus was found in the stools o f som.e of the members o f each of the families investigated, and it is suggested that means of spread is the faecal-oral route within -family groups. 